ile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br><br>Well, I am a gamer at heart and enjoy a great wargame, tabletop game, board game, card game, computer game (duh!), mind game, puzzle, whatever form of entertainment that is interactive rather then passive... I'm there!  <br><br>But my love is RPG for the depth and adventure.  I like the long saga that I'm deeply involved and engrossed in.<br><br>Anyways I'm leading up to something here.  Dungeon Siege and Morrowind are coming out soon and yes they look like great CRPGs in their own right but there is something special about them that hasn't been done before.  The developers of these very promising titles are releasing complete and robust mod tools for the gaming public.  This has been done before for FPS type games and I've dabbled in them but FPS is not my style.  <br><br>2 + 2 = 4<br><br>So, even though I've had this dream, I've never been able to get on a track to realizing it.  I've studied and studied the gaming hobby for this type of occassion and I'm very excited to give it a shot.  Though I shine in the knowledge department (and I feel I have a strong sense of what makes a game tick or not), my skillset is rather minimal.  I am a very quick learner so I'm not daunted by this obstacle.  One of the big obstacles that I am unsure of however is what exactly I should concentrate on.  I have an affinity for math and my brain works very well in 3D (I've done some autocad 3d before), but I am drawn to the actual design and function of a game, specifically the users experience.<br><br>I'd like to hear if any other Hawks out there have mod or game development experience or desire?  What do you think?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/ufernus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fernus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://silverhawks.freeservers.com/images/druidlogo.gif" BORDER=0></span><br>