mers.com/i/icons/characters/wizard.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Game Development &amp; Modding</span><hr size=1> Well Fernus, those days of poor game programmers are past.  Everything I've been reading on the current job market for this line of work is very promising.  I was reading about the recent game developers conference that just took place last weekend (or the weekend before) and the head hunters were out in full force.  For example, nvidia stated they were hiring about 500 people this coming year and currently they are hiring about 50/month.<br><br>Oh, and I'm with you on dungeon siege.  They used gmax for their modeling and it's going to be included in the toolset they are putting out for download when the game is launched <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Anyone else remotely interested in tooling around with the Dungeon Siege engine?  Even if we only end up creating a sub-mod that has a story etc. without additional sounds and graphics.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uquasimo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quasimo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/25/02 5:31:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/udarkarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br>  Posts: 483<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(3/26/02 12:44:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm69.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Game Development &amp; Modding</span><hr size=1> You know im there bro <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www